Being anxiouS, however, to see something of the world, to win his spurs, and to make a fortune, perhaps, in the provinces, Trebatius set out for the Roman camp in Gaul, carrying with him this letter of recommen- dation. Cicero's relations with Trebatius were of a most intimate nature, as his seventeen letters to him (Fam. 7. 6-22) prove.
